  "instructions": [
    "Preheat oven to 375°F (190°C).",
    "Grease a 9x13-inch baking dish with the melted ground nut oil.",
    "In a large bowl, combine the ground almonds, dates, coconut sugar, eggs, vanilla extract, ground cinnamon, ground nutmeg, and salt.",
    "Mix well until a dough forms.",
    "Press the dough into the prepared baking dish.",
    "Bake for 35 minutes.",
    "While the nuts bake, prepare the glaze by whisking together the maple syrup and 1 tablespoon of water.",
    "After the nuts have baked for 35 minutes, brush the glaze over the top of the nuts.",
    "Return the nuts to the oven and bake for an additional 5-7 minutes, or until the glaze is set.",
    "Remove from oven and let cool for 10 minutes before slicing and serving.",
    "Serve warm, garnished with fresh fruit or whipped cream if desired."
  ],
